This article summarizes Vice President Mike Pence's remarks during a speech in West Virginia. Pence addressed a train accident that occurred earlier that day, expressing condolences for the families affected. He then praised President Donald Trump and his administration's accomplishments, including an increase in defense spending, progress in national security, and the repeal of certain regulations. Pence also highlighted the tax cuts and tax reform bill signed into law, which he claimed has already led to economic growth and job creation. He criticized Senator Joe Manchin for voting against the tax cuts and other policies supported by the administration. Pence concluded by discussing the administration's future agenda, including infrastructure, immigration reform, and combating the opioid crisis. He encouraged the people of West Virginia to have faith and continue doing good in their communities.